03/04/2011
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina -- Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) football team is suspended from all international competitions, football governing bodies FIFA and UEFA announced on Friday (April 1st).
The federation had to change its statute replacing the three-member presidency by a single president by Thursday.
Bosnian representative and club teams are no longer entitled to take part in international competitions until the problem is resolved.
(RTRS, Nezavisne Novine, RTS - 01/04/11)
